The shortest distance traveled by the gecko is therefore equal to the length of the hypotenuse of the right triangle formed by the room. Using the Pythagorean theorem, we find that the shortest distance traveled by the gecko is \begin{align*}
\text{distance} &= \sqrt{(10+1)^2+(12+1)^2}\\
